<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1193] Potential infinite loop in nonblocking_server</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1193</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1187&quot; title=&quot;nonblocking_server shutdown race under Ruby 1.9&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1187&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1187&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; could cause the server to enter an infinite loop if select() started throwing Errno::EBADF when called on a non-closed @server_transport.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The obvious fix is to turn the &apos;next&apos; into a &apos;break&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
